<H1>Configuration reference</H1></DIV>
<DIV class=3Dcontent>
<P>This document is the index/reference page for all available core=20
configuration options in EditArea.</P>
<DIV class=3Dseparator></DIV>
<H2>Configuration options</H2>
<P>All configuration options below is to be placed within the init =
JavaScript=20
call.<BR>
<UL class=3Doptionlist>
  <LI><STRONG>Needed option</STRONG>=20
  <UL>
    <LI><STRONG>id</STRONG>: should contain the id of the textarea that =
should=20
    be converted into an editor <BR><SPAN class=3Dunderline>Type</SPAN>: =
String=20
    <BR><SPAN class=3Dunderline>Default</SPAN>: null </LI></UL><BR>
  <LI><STRONG>General</STRONG>=20
  <UL>
    <LI><STRONG>language</STRONG>: should contain a code of the language =
pack to=20
    be used for translation. If EditArea doesn't have a language pack =
for your=20
    language you could always write your own and contribute this back to =
this=20
    project by uploading it as a Patch at <A=20
    href=3D"http://sourceforge.net/projects/editarea/">SourceForge</A>. =
<BR><SPAN=20
    class=3Dunderline>Type</SPAN>: String <BR><SPAN=20
    class=3Dunderline>Default</SPAN>: "en"=20
    <LI><STRONG>syntax</STRONG>: should contain a code of the syntax =
definition=20
    file that must be used for the highlight mode. <BR><SPAN=20
    class=3Dunderline>Type</SPAN>: String <BR><SPAN=20
    class=3Dunderline>Default</SPAN>: ""=20
    <LI><STRONG>start_highlight</STRONG>: set if the editor should start =
with=20
    highlighted syntax displayed. <BR><SPAN =
class=3Dunderline>Type</SPAN>: Boolean=20
    <BR><SPAN class=3Dunderline>Default</SPAN>: false=20
    <LI><STRONG>is_multi_files</STRONG>: determine if the editor load =
the=20
    content of the textarea (false) or if it wait for an openFile() call =
for=20
    allowing file editing. <BR><SPAN class=3Dunderline>Type</SPAN>: =
Boolean=20
    <BR><SPAN class=3Dunderline>Default</SPAN>: false=20
    <LI><STRONG>min_width</STRONG>: define the minimum width of the =
editor=20
    <BR><SPAN class=3Dunderline>Type</SPAN>: Integer <BR><SPAN=20
    class=3Dunderline>Default</SPAN>: 400=20
    <LI><STRONG>min_height</STRONG>: define the minimum height of the =
editor=20
    <BR><SPAN class=3Dunderline>Type</SPAN>: Integer <BR><SPAN=20
    class=3Dunderline>Default</SPAN>: 100=20
    <LI><STRONG>allow_resize</STRONG>: define one with axis the editor =
can be=20
    resized by the user. <BR><SPAN class=3Dunderline>Type</SPAN>: String =
("no" (no=20
    resize allowed), "both" (x and y axis), "x", "y") <BR><SPAN=20
    class=3Dunderline>Default</SPAN>: "both"=20
    <LI><STRONG>allow_toggle</STRONG>: define if a toggle button must be =
added=20
    under the editor in order to allow to toggle between the editor and =
the=20
    orginal textarea. <BR><SPAN class=3Dunderline>Type</SPAN>: Boolean =
<BR><SPAN=20
    class=3Dunderline>Default</SPAN>: true=20
    <LI><STRONG>plugins</STRONG>: a comma separated list of plugins to =
load.=20
    <BR><SPAN class=3Dunderline>Type</SPAN>: String <BR><SPAN=20
    class=3Dunderline>Default</SPAN>: ""=20
    <LI><STRONG>browsers</STRONG>: define if the editor must be loaded =
only when=20
    the user navigotr is known to be a working one, or if it will be =
loaded for=20
    all navigators. <BR><SPAN class=3Dunderline>Type</SPAN>: String =
("all" or=20
    "known") <BR><SPAN class=3Dunderline>Default</SPAN>: "known"=20
    <LI><STRONG>display</STRONG>: specify when the textarea will be =
converted=20
    into an editor. If set to "later", the toogle button will be =
displayed to=20
    allow later conversion. <BR><SPAN class=3Dunderline>Type</SPAN>: =
String=20
    ("onload" or "later") <BR><SPAN class=3Dunderline>Default</SPAN>: =
"onload"=20
    <LI><STRONG>toolbar</STRONG>: define the toolbar that will be =
displayed,=20
    each element being separated by a ",". <BR><SPAN=20
    class=3Dunderline>Type</SPAN>: String (combinaison of: "|", "*", =
"search",=20
    "go_to_line", "undo", "redo", "change_smooth_selection", =
"reset_highlight",=20
    "highlight", "help", "save", "load", "new_document", =
"syntax_selection")=20
    <BR>"|" or "separator" make appears a separator in the toolbar. =
<BR>"*" or=20
    "return" make appears a line-break in the toolbar <BR><SPAN=20
    class=3Dunderline>Default</SPAN>: "search, go_to_line, fullscreen, =
|, undo,=20
    redo, |, select_font,|, change_smooth_selection, highlight, =
reset_highlight,=20
    |, help"=20
    <LI><STRONG>begin_toolbar</STRONG>: toolbar button list to add =
before the=20
    toolbar defined by the "toolbar" option. <BR><SPAN=20
    class=3Dunderline>Type</SPAN>: String (cf. "toolbar" option) =
<BR><SPAN=20
    class=3Dunderline>Default</SPAN>: ""=20
    <LI><STRONG>end_toolbar</STRONG>: toolbar button list to add after =
the=20
    toolbar defined by the "toolbar" option. <BR><SPAN=20
    class=3Dunderline>Type</SPAN>: String (cf. "toolbar" option) =
<BR><SPAN=20
    class=3Dunderline>Default</SPAN>: ""=20
    <LI><STRONG>font_size</STRONG>: define the font-size used to display =
the=20
    text in the editor. <BR><SPAN class=3Dunderline>Type</SPAN>: Integer =
<BR><SPAN=20
    class=3Dunderline>Default</SPAN>: 10=20
    <LI><STRONG>font_family</STRONG>: define the font-familly used to =
display=20
    the text in the editor. (eg: "monospace" or "verdana,monospace"). =
Opera will=20
    always use "monospace". <BR><SPAN class=3Dunderline>Type</SPAN>: =
String=20
    <BR><SPAN class=3Dunderline>Default</SPAN>: "monospace"=20
    <LI><STRONG>gecko_spellcheck</STRONG>: allow to disable/enable the =
Firefox 2=20
    spellchecker <BR><SPAN class=3Dunderline>Type</SPAN>: Boolean =
<BR><SPAN=20
    class=3Dunderline>Default</SPAN>: false=20
    <LI><STRONG>max_undo</STRONG>: number of undo action allowed =
<BR><SPAN=20
    class=3Dunderline>Type</SPAN>: Integer <BR><SPAN=20
    class=3Dunderline>Default</SPAN>: 20=20
    <LI><STRONG>fullscreen</STRONG>: determine if EditArea start in =
fullscreen=20
    mode or not <BR><SPAN class=3Dunderline>Type</SPAN>: Boolean =
<BR><SPAN=20
    class=3Dunderline>Default</SPAN>: false=20
    <LI><STRONG>replace_tab_by_spaces</STRONG>: define the number of =
spaces that=20
    will replace tabulations (\t) in text. If tabulation should stay =
tabulation,=20
    set this option to false. <BR><SPAN class=3Dunderline>Type</SPAN>: =
Integer (or=20
    false) <BR><SPAN class=3Dunderline>Default</SPAN>: false=20
    <LI><STRONG>debug</STRONG>: used to display some debug information =
into a=20
    newly created textarea. Can be usefull to display trace info in it =
if you=20
    want to modify the code. <BR><SPAN class=3Dunderline>Type</SPAN>: =
Boolean=20
    <BR><SPAN class=3Dunderline>Default</SPAN>: false </LI></UL><BR>
  <LI><STRONG>Callback</STRONG>=20
  <UL>
    <LI><STRONG>load_callback</STRONG>: the function name that will be =
called=20
    when the user will press the "load" button in the toolbar. This =
function=20
    will reveice one parameter that will be the id of the textarea. You =
can=20
    update the content of the textarea by using =
"editAreaLoader.setValue(the_id,=20
    new_value);". <BR><SPAN class=3Dunderline>Type</SPAN>: String =
<BR><SPAN=20
    class=3Dunderline>Default</SPAN>: ""=20
    <LI><STRONG>save_callback</STRONG>: the function name that will be =
called=20
    when the user will press the "save" button in the toolbar. This =
function=20
    will reveice two parameters, the first being the id of the textarea =
and the=20
    second containing the content of the textarea. <BR><SPAN=20
    class=3Dunderline>Type</SPAN>: String <BR><SPAN=20
    class=3Dunderline>Default</SPAN>: ""=20
    <LI><STRONG>change_callback</STRONG>: the function name that will be =
called=20
    when the onchange event of the textarea of EditArea will be =
triggered. This=20
    function will reveice one parameter that will be the id of the =
textarea.=20
    Will be triggered only is EditArea is displayed. <BR><SPAN=20
    class=3Dunderline>Type</SPAN>: String <BR><SPAN=20
    class=3Dunderline>Default</SPAN>: ""=20
    <LI><STRONG>submit_callback</STRONG>: the function name that will be =
called=20
    when the form containing the EditArea will be submitted. This =
function will=20
    reveice one parameter that will be the id of the textarea. Will be =
triggered=20
    regardless the state of EditArea (displayed or not). <BR><SPAN=20
    class=3Dunderline>Type</SPAN>: String <BR><SPAN=20
    class=3Dunderline>Default</SPAN>: ""=20
    <LI><STRONG>EA_init_callback</STRONG>: the function name that will =
be called=20
    just after the editAreaLoader.init() function, once EditAreaLoader =
will be=20
    initalized but still not displayed. This function will reveice one =
parameter=20
    that will be the id of the textarea. <BR><SPAN =
class=3Dunderline>Type</SPAN>:=20
    String <BR><SPAN class=3Dunderline>Default</SPAN>: ""=20
    <LI><STRONG>EA_delete_callback</STRONG>: the function name that will =
be=20
    called when EditArea will be destroyed regardless the fact that it =
has been=20
    displayed or not. This function will reveice one parameter that will =
be the=20
    id of the textarea. <BR><SPAN class=3Dunderline>Type</SPAN>: String =
<BR><SPAN=20
    class=3Dunderline>Default</SPAN>: ""=20
    <LI><STRONG>EA_toggle_on_callback</STRONG>: the function name that =
will be=20
    called when EditArea will be toogled on for. This function will =
reveice one=20
    parameter that will be the id of the textarea. <BR><SPAN=20
    class=3Dunderline>Type</SPAN>: String <BR><SPAN=20
    class=3Dunderline>Default</SPAN>: ""=20
    <LI><STRONG>EA_toggle_off_callback</STRONG>: the function name that =
will be=20
    called when EditArea will be toggled off. This function will reveice =
one=20
    parameter that will be the id of the textarea. <BR><SPAN=20
    class=3Dunderline>Type</SPAN>: String <BR><SPAN=20
    class=3Dunderline>Default</SPAN>: ""=20
    <LI><STRONG>EA_load_callback</STRONG>: the function name that will =
be called=20
    when EditArea will be displayed for the first time. This function =
will=20
    reveice one parameter that will be the id of the textarea. <BR><SPAN =

    class=3Dunderline>Type</SPAN>: String <BR><SPAN=20
    class=3Dunderline>Default</SPAN>: ""=20
    <LI><STRONG>EA_unload_callback</STRONG>: the function name that will =
be=20
    called when EditArea will be destroyed (if it have been displayed at =
least=20
    one time). This function will reveice one parameter that will be the =
id of=20
    the textarea. <BR><SPAN class=3Dunderline>Type</SPAN>: String =
<BR><SPAN=20
    class=3Dunderline>Default</SPAN>: ""=20
    <LI><STRONG>EA_file_switch_on_callback</STRONG>: the function name =
that will=20
    be called when the tabulation of the file will be selected. This =
function=20
    will reveice one parameter that will be an associative array =
containing all=20
    file's infos. <BR><SPAN class=3Dunderline>Type</SPAN>: String =
<BR><SPAN=20
    class=3Dunderline>Default</SPAN>: ""=20
    <LI><STRONG>EA_file_switch_off_callback</STRONG>: the function name =
that=20
    will be called when the tabulation of the file will be blur (the =
file was=20
    selected, and another file receive focus). This function will =
reveice one=20
    parameter that will be an associative array containing all file =
infos.=20
    <BR><SPAN class=3Dunderline>Type</SPAN>: String <BR><SPAN=20
    class=3Dunderline>Default</SPAN>: ""=20
    <LI><STRONG>EA_file_close_callback</STRONG>: the function name that =
will be=20
    called when the tabulation of a file will be closed. This function =
will=20
    reveice one parameter that will be an associative array containing =
all file=20
    infos. <BR><SPAN class=3Dunderline>Type</SPAN>: String <BR><SPAN=20
    class=3Dunderline>Default</SPAN>: "" </LI></UL><BR></LI></UL>
<DIV class=3Dseparator></DIV>
<H2>Initialization of EditArea</H2>
<P>In order to initialize EditArea the following code must be placed =
within HEAD=20
element of a document. The following example is configurated to convert =
the=20
TEXTAREA element which has "textarea_1" as id into editor when the page =
loads.=20
The "id" option is the only obligatory option. <PRE>&lt;html&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
<STRONG>&lt;script language=3D"javascript" type=3D"text/javascript" =
src=3D"/editarea/edit_area/edit_area_full.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;script language=3D"javascript" type=3D"text/javascript"&gt;
editAreaLoader.init({
	id : "textarea_1"		// textarea id
	,syntax: "css"			// syntax to be uses for highgliting
	,start_highlight: true		// to display with highlight mode on start-up
});
&lt;/script&gt;</STRONG>
&lt;/head&gt;
</PRE>
<P></P>
<P>See the <A=20
href=3D"http://www.cdolivet.net/editarea/editarea/docs/include.html">incl=
ude</A>=20
document to learn more about the way to use the best script include. =
</P>
<P>If you want to convert several textarea on your webpage, just call =
several=20
time the init function with a different id parameter.</P></DIV>
